            <div class="col-lg-6 col-sm-12 col-xs-12" style="text-align: center;">
              <br>
              <p style="font-family: PlayfairDisplay-Regular; line-height: 1.5;">
                I am student from China and could not leave Australia on time to be with my family during hard corona time. This was very hard for me but what was also very hard that I experienced many discrimination and hate in the streets and internet. It sometimes made me so sad that I didn’t go out to buy food. 
                <br>
                <br>
I could understand that people were mad about Chinese customs and also political decisions. But this was not me and also not my friends. We don’t eat bats and we want everyone to live together in peace. I don’t want animal cruelty and I don’t want animal market. But things work differently in China. 
<br>
<br>
In my online class I asked the teacher to talk about this. He said yes and all students had a wonderful and respectful talk. Everyone explained their views and everyone understood that we are not that different. 
<br><br>
Becky

              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
