              <br>
              <p style="font-family: PlayfairDisplay-Regular; line-height: 1.5;">
             During the crisis my job got suspended. All my colleagues received financial help from the government since they were residents but I didn’t. I was furious. I pay the same amount of taxes as them but don’t receive anything for it. This is so unfair, I would even say discriminating. 
             <br><br>
With no other jobs available, I had to make an my uber eats account and deliver food to people. After days of working in frustration, I realized that my situation wasn’t actually that bad. I loved being out on the road, making people happy when they received their food and being able to take hot shower after a rainy night of deliveries. 
<br><br>
I was happy with my individual situation, exactly how it was. It just took me some time to understand that – my situation was good as it was. 
<br><br>
Ben

              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
