              <p style="font-family: PlayfairDisplay-Regular; line-height: 1.5;">
              Yes I lost my job, yes I lost my savings, yes I am behind my rent. But, believe it or not, I am somehow happier than before. When the quarantine measures started, I stopped smoking … I admit due to financial reasons but hey…, I ran 2km every day … started with 200 m and then was puffed so that I had to walk the rest… and I read two books. 
              <br><br>
These achievements make me happy. I feel more energetic and healthy. And this reflects on how I approach and see people. I was never unfriendly or rude but people annoyed me a lot. I complained about them to myself. Now that I am happier with myself I am more positive and patient with people… Interesting.  
<br><br>
Joe

